### IdeaSnap REST API Test Cases
# Use VS Code REST Client plugin or IntelliJ HTTP Client to execute these queries directly.
# Default base url is http://localhost:8080. Update as needed.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:28080

### 1. Register Alice (User)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "email": "alice@ideasnap.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "bio": "Senior Java Developer | Spring & Kubernetes expert",
  "profileImage": "https://api.dicebear.com/7.x/adventurer/svg?seed=alice"
}

### 2. Register Bob (User)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bob",
  "email": "bob@ideasnap.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "bio": "AI Engineer | DevOps and Kubernetes enthusiast",
  "profileImage": "https://api.dicebear.com/7.x/adventurer/svg?seed=bob"
}

### 3. Login as Alice (To obtain Access and Refresh Tokens)
# @name aliceLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Capture Alice Tokens from Login response
@aliceAccessToken = {{aliceLogin.response.body.accessToken}}
@aliceRefreshToken = {{aliceLogin.response.body.refreshToken}}


### 4. Login as Bob (To obtain Access and Refresh Tokens)
# @name bobLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bob",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Capture Bob Tokens from Login response
@bobAccessToken = {{bobLogin.response.body.accessToken}}
@bobRefreshToken = {{bobLogin.response.body.refreshToken}}


### 5. Refresh Access Token (Uses Alice's Refresh Token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{aliceRefreshToken}}"
}


### 6. Create Public Post as Alice (With Tags and Markdown)
# @name createPostAlice
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/posts
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{aliceAccessToken}}

{
  "title": "Mastering Spring Boot 3.x Virtual Threads",
  "content": "### What are Virtual Threads?\nVirtual threads are lightweight threads that reduce the overhead of writing, maintaining, and debugging high-throughput concurrent applications. \n\nTo enable them in **Spring Boot 3.x**, just add this to your properties:\n```yaml\nspring.threads.virtual.enabled: true\n```\nThis maps Tomcat's request handler execution to use virtual threads instead of platform threads. Highly recommended for I/O heavy apps!",
  "tags": ["Spring", "Java", "DevOps"],
  "visibility": "PUBLIC",
  "expiresInMinutes": 60
}

### Capture Created Post ID
@postId = {{createPostAlice.response.body.id}}


### 7. Create Private Post as Bob
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/posts
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bobAccessToken}}

{
  "title": "My Private AI Architecture Draft",
  "content": "Secret configurations for fine-tuning LLMs on local cluster. Internal use only.",
  "tags": ["AI", "Kubernetes"],
  "visibility": "PRIVATE"
}


### 8. Fetch Single Post by ID (Public Access)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/posts/{{postId}}
Accept: application/json


### 9. Get Public Feed (Latest Posts - default)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/posts?sort=latest&page=0&size=10
Accept: application/json


### 10. Get Public Feed (Trending Posts)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/posts?sort=trending&page=0&size=10
Accept: application/json


### 11. React to Post (Bob reacts INSIGHTFUL to Alice's post)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/posts/{{postId}}/reactions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bobAccessToken}}

{
  "reactionType": "INSIGHTFUL"
}


### 12. Fetch Alice's Post Again (To verify reaction count & Bob's active reaction type)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/posts/{{postId}}
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bobAccessToken}}


### 13. Remove Reaction (Bob removes reaction)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/posts/{{postId}}/reactions
Authorization: Bearer {{bobAccessToken}}


### 14. Comment on Post (Bob comments on Alice's post)
# @name createComment
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/posts/{{postId}}/comments
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bobAccessToken}}

{
  "content": "This is amazing! Virtual threads are a game-changer for high concurrency environments."
}

### Capture Created Comment ID
@commentId = {{createComment.response.body.id}}


### 15. Get Comments for Alice's Post
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/posts/{{postId}}/comments?page=0&size=5
Accept: application/json


### 16. Delete Comment (Bob deletes his own comment)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/comments/{{commentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{bobAccessToken}}


### 17. Follow Alice (Bob follows Alice)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/alice/follow
Authorization: Bearer {{bobAccessToken}}


### 18. Get Followers of Alice (Should include Bob)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/alice/followers?page=0&size=10
Accept: application/json


### 19. Get Following list of Bob (Should include Alice)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/bob/following?page=0&size=10
Accept: application/json


### 20. Unfollow Alice (Bob unfollows Alice)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/alice/unfollow
Authorization: Bearer {{bobAccessToken}}


### 21. Get User Profile (Get Alice's profile info)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/alice
Accept: application/json


### 22. Update User Profile (Alice updates her bio)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/profile
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{aliceAccessToken}}

{
  "bio": "Principal Architect & Java Champion | Developer Advocate",
  "profileImage": "https://api.dicebear.com/7.x/adventurer/svg?seed=aliceUpdated"
}


### 23. Search Posts by Tag (Search 'Spring')
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/search?tag=Spring&page=0&size=10
Accept: application/json


### 24. Search Posts by Username (Search author 'alice')
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/search?username=alice&page=0&size=10
Accept: application/json


### 25. Search Posts by Title (Search query 'Mastering')
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/search?query=Mastering&page=0&size=10
Accept: application/json


### 26. Delete Post (Alice deletes her own post)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/posts/{{postId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{aliceAccessToken}}


### 27. Logout (Invalidates Alice's session and token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{aliceAccessToken}}
